[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi everyone! I should probably quickly introduce myself, I am working on behalf of NVIDIA to help bring up the Nova driver. One of the things I have been focusing on is having a clean and safe way to read and write hardware registers and their fields, and for this I have submitted the following macro:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20250320-registers-v2-1-d277409bcde8@nvidia.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20250320-registers-v2-1-d277409bcde8@nvidia.com/</a></p>\n<p>Since it can be helpful outside of Nova as well, it has been suggested to submit it as a general R4L patch, not just a Nova one.</p>\n<p>It is still a bit rough around the edges though, and another suggestion was to rewrite it as a procedural macro. Which I have tried doing with my limited knowledge of the matter, but to my embarrassment I couldn't even produce a working Hello world macro using a simple <code>quote! { }</code>. <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span> Rust procedural macros in the kernel seems to be more limited than for userspace, and I have been trying to find an anchor point in existing code from which I could grow my own macro, but to no avail.</p>\n<p>I know this sounds a bit vague, but could I get some suggestions to get started with this? Even a pointer to a minimal working in-kernel procedural macro would be helpful.</p>",
        "id": 508643942,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743122472
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>can you post the code that you tried? It <em>should</em> be pretty simple, create a new function in <code>rust/macros/lib.rs</code> with the name of your macro, put <code>#[proc_macro]</code> on top of it and then delegate to some file in which you define your proc macro like the other files in <code>rust/macros</code>.</p>\n<p>Appending this to <code>rust/macros/lib.rs</code> works for me:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// foo</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[proc_macro]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">input</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 508646144,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743123873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"890884\">Alexandre Courbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Defining.20the.20layout.20of.20registers.20using.20macros/near/508643942\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Rust procedural macros in the kernel seems to be more limited than for userspace</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>unfortunately yes, we're working on getting <code>syn</code> support, but it'll probably still take at least a couple of cycles</p>",
        "id": 508646195,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743123924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Uh that's interesting, pasting your code into <code>rust/macros/lib.rs</code> I get this error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0282</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">annotations</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">needed</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">46</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">22</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">46</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"n\">tokens</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">vec</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">                      </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"p\">:::</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">499</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">499</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">---------</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invocation</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">originates</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">quote_spanned</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">which</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">comes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expansion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nightly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">builds</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">backtrace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">more</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">info</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0283</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">annotations</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">needed</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">9</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from_iter</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tokens</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"p\">:::</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">499</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">499</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">---------</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invocation</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">multiple</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">satisfying</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">FromIterator</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">FromIterator</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">FromIterator</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenTree</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">proc_macro</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">TokenStream</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">originates</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">quote_spanned</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">which</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">comes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expansion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nightly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">builds</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">macro</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">backtrace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">more</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">info</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">aborting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">previous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">errors</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>My tree is still based on <code>v6.14-rc5</code>, maybe it's different with <code>rust-next</code>?</p>\n<p>For reference, what I tried was the same as you with the exception that I tried to output something using <code>quote! {}</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">quote</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">hello_world</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello, World!\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But I am obviously misusing it somehow.</p>",
        "id": 508647848,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743124943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>huh that's weird, do you have a lot of patches on <code>v6.14-rc5</code>? If yes, then could you try it on any recent tag or <code>rust-next</code>?</p>",
        "id": 508647934,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125030
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah let me try that, actually that's what I should have done before replying, sorry</p>",
        "id": 508648002,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no worries :)</p>",
        "id": 508648018,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yep, it passes with <code>rust-next</code>! Looks like that was part of my problem :)</p>",
        "id": 508648279,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125228
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for looking into it</p>",
        "id": 508648382,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125283
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm still wondering whether we could not achieve something good enough using declarative macros... Procedural macros will probably take longer to expand, and this macro will probably be called many many times (once per register), which has the potential to add up in compilation times</p>",
        "id": 508648481,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125347
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if we go the procedural route there is also going to be a tension between the wait for the required support (e.g. <code>syn</code>?) to land, vs. the will to merge code into nova-core quickly</p>",
        "id": 508648662,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125447
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and I'm not even sure that this is how we will want to access register fields in the kernel to begin with :)</p>",
        "id": 508648715,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743125475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"890884\">Alexandre Courbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Defining.20the.20layout.20of.20registers.20using.20macros/near/508648382\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks for looking into it</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I found the patch in rust-next that makes <code>quote! {}</code> work: <code>85525eda4f13</code> (\"rust: macros: support additional tokens in quote!\")</p>",
        "id": 508648864,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"890884\">Alexandre Courbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Defining.20the.20layout.20of.20registers.20using.20macros/near/508648715\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>and I'm not even sure that this is how we will want to access register fields in the kernel to begin with :)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'm even less of an authority on that (no idea what register fields are :)</p>\n<p>I can only recommend to work via use-cases create something that will work with both simple and complex cases (if simple ones are the majority, then it also makes sense to have a shorthand for that).</p>",
        "id": 508649044,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"890884\">Alexandre Courbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Defining.20the.20layout.20of.20registers.20using.20macros/near/508648662\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>if we go the procedural route there is also going to be a tension between the wait for the required support (e.g. <code>syn</code>?) to land, vs. the will to merge code into nova-core quickly</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would not wait for <code>syn</code></p>",
        "id": 508649106,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125677
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"890884\">Alexandre Courbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Defining.20the.20layout.20of.20registers.20using.20macros/near/508648481\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm still wondering whether we could not achieve something good enough using declarative macros... Procedural macros will probably take longer to expand, and this macro will probably be called many many times (once per register), which has the potential to add up in compilation times</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I haven't taken a close look yet, but the macros that you wrote seem to be rather complex. So writing them as proc-macros is probably a good idea. Although writing the parsing without <code>syn</code> is going to be challenging.</p>\n<p>I don't know the exact impact on performance of compile times, AFAIK the greatest impact comes from having proc-macros in the first place.</p>",
        "id": 508649328,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1743125823
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I looked into this last year and found that the embedded rust community has a very cool solution for typed register access. A good example is <a href=\"https://github.com/stm32-rs/stm32-rs\">https://github.com/stm32-rs/stm32-rs</a> . The data source is SVD provided by vendor with some cleanup: <a href=\"https://github.com/embassy-rs/stm32-data\">https://github.com/embassy-rs/stm32-data</a></p>",
        "id": 508669710,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1743138320
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder if something similar could be used in the kernel?</p>",
        "id": 508669851,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1743138401
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The regmap abstraction I submitted a while ago also define the layout of the registers through macros: <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/8b85fbfa-ffb5-48d0-ba7b-0e26001ab3ae@sirena.org.uk/T/#u\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/8b85fbfa-ffb5-48d0-ba7b-0e26001ab3ae@sirena.org.uk/T/#u</a><br>\nWould be good the layout interface defined for raw registers and for regmap registers is similar.</p>",
        "id": 508843799,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabien Parent",
        "timestamp": 1743195299
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, both the stm32 solution and regmap abstraction look very relevant, I'll take a look at both. <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"585586\">@Fabien Parent</span>, are you planning to keep pushing this patchset?</p>",
        "id": 509429439,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexandre Courbot",
        "timestamp": 1743508058
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"890884\">@Alexandre Courbot</span>: yes, a v2 will be submitted.</p>",
        "id": 509530651,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabien Parent",
        "timestamp": 1743535338
    }
]